Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna The Election Petitions Tribunal  in Kaduna on Wednesday  dismissed a petition  filed  by Senator Shehu Sani challenging  Uba Sani’s victory in the February 23  Kaduna Central senatorial election. Delivering judgment on the petition,   the  chairman of the tribunal, Justice A. H. Suleiman,  said the petition lacked  merit. Uba Sani, who was  the candidate of the All Progressives Congress for the polls, won  with 355,242 votes, while Lawal Adamu of the  Peoples Democratic Party came second  with  195,497 votes. Sani, who represented  the People’s Redemption Party, placed  third with 70,613 votes. In a two-hour judgment, Justice  Suleiman said they decided to dismiss Sani’s petition  based on  the  evidence presented before the tribunal. Eighteen petitions was  filed before the  tribunal regarding the National Assembly  and  state House of Assembly  elections in Kaduna State. Copyright PUNCH.
